statements: SELECT log_id, user_id, event_type, authentication_time, success FROM AuthenticationLogs;
SELECT user_id, log_id, event_type, authentication_time, success FROM AuthenticationLogs;
SELECT log_id, user_id, authentication_time, event_type, success FROM AuthenticationLogs ORDER BY authentication_time DESC;
SELECT log_id, user_id, event_type, authentication_time, success FROM AuthenticationLogs WHERE success = true;
SELECT user_id, event_type, success, authentication_time, log_id FROM AuthenticationLogs ORDER BY user_id;
SELECT * FROM AuthenticationLogs WHERE success = TRUE ORDER BY authentication_time DESC LIMIT 10
SELECT log_id, user_id, authentication_time FROM AuthenticationLogs WHERE event_type = 'login' ORDER BY authentication_time ASC
SELECT user_id, COUNT(log_id) AS total_logs FROM AuthenticationLogs GROUP BY user_id HAVING COUNT(log_id) > 5
SELECT DISTINCT user_id FROM AuthenticationLogs WHERE success = FALSE
SELECT * FROM AuthenticationLogs WHERE authentication_time BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-01-31'
SELECT * FROM authentication_logs;
SELECT user_id, event_description, event_timestamp FROM authentication_logs;
SELECT log_id, user_id, event_description, event_timestamp FROM authentication_logs ORDER BY event_timestamp DESC;
SELECT * FROM authentication_logs WHERE user_id = 123;
SELECT log_id, user_id, event_timestamp FROM authentication_logs WHERE event_description LIKE '%login%';
SELECT * FROM authentication_logs WHERE user_id = 5 AND event_timestamp > '2022-01-01'
SELECT user_id, event_description FROM authentication_logs WHERE log_id BETWEEN 100 AND 200 ORDER BY event_timestamp DESC
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_logs FROM authentication_logs
SELECT DISTINCT user_id FROM authentication_logs ORDER BY user_id
SELECT user_id, COUNT(*) AS total_trails FROM audit_trails GROUP BY user_id HAVING total_trails > 1 ORDER BY total_trails DESC
